label.value: Not More Than
Sufficient Quantity
Glottic Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of glottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of subglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Supraglottic Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of subglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Glottic Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of glottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Stage IIA Bone Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IIA includes: T1, N0, M0, G3, G4.  T1: Tumor 8 cm or less in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G3: Poorly differentiated.  G4: Undifferentiated. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor limited to the vocal cord(s) (may involve anterior or posterior commissure) with normal mobility. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor limited to one vocal cord. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor involving both vocal cords. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor extending to supraglottis and/or subglottis, and/or with impaired vocal cord mobility. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor limited to the larynx with vocal cord fixation and /or invading paraglottic space, and/or minor thyroid cartilage erosion (e.g. inner cortex). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor invading through thyroid cartilage and/or invading tissues beyond the larynx (e.g. trachea, soft tissues of neck including deep extrinsic muscle of the tongue, strap muscles, thyroid, or esophagus). (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Glottic cancer with tumor invading prevertebral space, encasing carotid artery, or invading mediastinal structures. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Bone Sarcoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: T3, N0, M0, G3, G4. T3: Tumor more than 8 cm in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  G3: Poorly differentiated.  G4: Undifferentiated. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of glottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Glottic Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Glottic cancer with no distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Glottic cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of glottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Glottic Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm, but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with metastasis in two or more ipsilateral nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Osteosarcoma Arising in Paget Disease of Bone

value.value: A sarcomatous transformation of pre-existing Paget disease of the bone. Osteosarcomas arising from Paget disease of the bone are high grade lesions and usually have a poor prognosis.

label.value: Glottic Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer with metastasis in a lymph node, more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Glottic Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Glottic cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Centigray

value.value: The metric unit of absorbed radiation dose equal to the absorption of one hundredth of joule of radiation energy per kilogram of matter.

label.value: Grid Service Operation

value.value: An action, exposed through a Grid Service's interface, which requests some service-side processing to occur, optionally taking one or more inputs, and under normal processing, optionally returning one or more outputs.

label.value: Grid Service Fault

value.value: The result of execution of a Grid Service Operation when an unexpected or illegal event occurs during processing, generally indicating through a message and/or additional details, the cause of abnormal execution.

label.value: Caplet Dosing Unit

value.value: A dosing unit equal to the amount of active ingredient(s) contained in a caplet.

label.value: Deciliter

value.value: The unit of volume equal to one tenth of a liter. Accepted for use with the SI.

label.value: Decimeter

value.value: The metric unit of length equal to one tenth of a meter.

label.value: Methylprednisolone

value.value: A synthetic corticosteroid with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating properties.  Methylprednisolone binds to and activates specific nuclear receptors, resulting in altered gene expression and inhibition of proinflammatory cytokine production.  This agent also decreases the number of circulating lymphocytes, induces cell differentiation, and stimulates apoptosis in sensitive tumor cell populations.

label.value: Multifocal Osteosarcoma

value.value: A primary bone osteosarcoma affecting multiple bone sites.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of subglottic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Subglottic cancer with no distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Subglottic cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm, but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with metastasis in two or more ipsilateral nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Synchronous Multifocal Osteosarcoma

value.value: A bone osteosarcoma affecting multiple skeletal sites, with multifocal lesions discovered within 6 months of the appearance of the initial tumor.  It has a poor prognosis.

label.value: Subglottic Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Subglottic cancer with metastasis in a lymph node, more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)
